    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>By mid-decade the arctic will have no ice for part of the summer.</p>
<p>When the arctic has no summer ice all the water is above freezing.</p>
<p>When the water is above freezing the nearby land is also above freezing.</p>
<p>When the nearby land is above freezing the methane comes out.</p>
<p>When the methane comes out the global temperature rises.</p>
<p>When global temperature rises the next summer no-ice period will be longer.</p>
<p>Lather, rinse, repeat...</p>
<p>It's something of a simplification but I find it gets the point across.</p>

