<p>We must find a way to re-sequester surface water and rain run-off BACK into the aquifers. Right now it takes years if not decades for surface water to reach the aquifers. But <a href="http://lubbockonline.com/local-news/2013-02-18/potential-recharging-ogallala-west-texas-needs-more-study#.UfWu29LVCSo">this article</a> suggests what I have been proposing for some time: That we ADAPT to climate change, find ways to save potable water from evaporation and over-use. And find a way to funnel seasonal monsoons (yes, we have them) into the aquifers instead of running off into the ocean, carrying fertile land and the poisons we put on it.</p>

